I understand that you want to implement the RK4 method in your code. You can modify the given LastNameFirstInit_Lab8 function to use the RK4 method instead of the ABM3 method. Here's the modified function using the provided RK4 chunk:

```MATLAB
function LastNameFirstInit_Lab8(function_handles, initial_augmented_state, step_size, num_steps)
    % Initialize the state array
    augmented_state_array = zeros(num_steps + 1, numel(initial_augmented_state));
    augmented_state_array(1, :) = initial_augmented_state;

    % Initialize variables
    num_state_vars = numel(initial_augmented_state) - 1;
    h = step_size;

    % Compute the solution using the RK4 method
    for iter = 1:num_steps
        state = augmented_state_array(iter,:);
        slopes = zeros(4, num_state_vars);
        for c = 1:num_state_vars
            slopes(1, c) = function_handles{c}(state);
        end

        state = augmented_state_array(iter, :) + (h / 2) * [1, slopes(1, :)];
        for c = 1:num_state_vars
            slopes(2, c) = function_handles{c}(state);
        end

        state = augmented_state_array(iter, :) + (h / 2) * [1, slopes(2, :)];
        for c = 1:num_state_vars
            slopes(3, c) = function_handles{c}(state);
        end

        state = augmented_state_array(iter, :) + h * [1, slopes(3, :)];
        for c = 1:num_state_vars
            slopes(4, c) = function_handles{c}(state);
        end

        RK = (slopes(1,:) + 2 * slopes(2,:) + 2 * slopes(3,:) + slopes(4,:)) / 6;
        augmented_state_array(iter + 1, :) = augmented_state_array(iter, :) + h * [1, RK];
    end

    % Print the final state
    fprintf('Final state of the system: \n');
    disp(augmented_state_array(end, :));

    % Plot the results for each dependent variable
    for i = 1:num_state_vars
        figure;
        plot(augmented_state_array(:, 1), augmented_state_array(:, i + 1));
        title(['Var' num2str(i)]);
        xlabel('t');
        ylabel(['Var' num2str(i)]);
    end
end
```

Now, you can use this function in the main script provided earlier, and it will use the RK4 method instead of the ABM3 method to solve the system. Run the main script in MATLAB with this modified function to obtain the system's natural frequency and mode shape using the RK4 method.

在C#中，CookieContainer类不包含remove方法。如果需要删除CookieContainer中的某个Cookie，可以采用以下方式：

1. 创建一个新的CookieContainer实例。
2. 遍历旧的CookieContainer中的所有Cookie，将需要保留的Cookie添加到新的CookieContainer中。
3. 使用新的CookieContainer实例替换旧的实例。

以下是一个例子：

```csharp
using System;
using System.Net;

class Program
{
    static void Main()
    {
        // 创建一个CookieContainer实例，并添加一些Cookie
        CookieContainer container = new CookieContainer();
        container.Add(new Cookie("Cookie1", "Value1", "/", "example.com"));
        container.Add(new Cookie("Cookie2", "Value2", "/", "example.com"));
        container.Add(new Cookie("Cookie3", "Value3", "/", "example.com"));

        Console.WriteLine("Before removing cookie:");
        DisplayCookies(container, "example.com");

        // 移除名为"Cookie2"的Cookie
        string cookieNameToRemove = "Cookie2";
        CookieContainer newContainer = new CookieContainer();
        Uri uri = new Uri("http://example.com");
        foreach (Cookie cookie in container.GetCookies(uri))
        {
            if (cookie.Name != cookieNameToRemove)
            {
                newContainer.Add(cookie);
            }
        }

        container = newContainer;

        Console.WriteLine("\nAfter removing cookie:");
        DisplayCookies(container, "example.com");
    }

    static void DisplayCookies(CookieContainer container, string domain)
    {
        Uri uri = new Uri("http://" + domain);
        foreach (Cookie cookie in container.GetCookies(uri))
        {
            Console.WriteLine("Name: " + cookie.Name + ", Value: " + cookie.Value);
        }
    }
}
```

这个例子首先创建了一个包含3个Cookie的CookieContainer实例。然后，我们创建一个新的CookieContainer实例，将除了名为"Cookie2"的Cookie之外的其他Cookie添加到新的实例。最后，我们用新的CookieContainer实例替换旧的实例。

